<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 01 at 6:18PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
southwestern Campbell County through 645 PM EDT...
At 618 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Evington, moving southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Altavista...
Hurt...
Evington...
Gladys...
Hodges...
and Timberlake.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
